13
00:01:23,520 --> 00:01:29,330
By chance, have you ever seen me before the practice game?

14
00:01:29,330 --> 00:01:32,370
We're neighbors, so I'm just wondering if we've seen each other as we've come and gone.

15
00:01:32,370 --> 00:01:33,640
I have.

16
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:35,900
Really?

17
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:39,590
You mistook me for the package delivery guy before.

18
00:01:39,590 --> 00:01:41,230
I don't think you remember.

19
00:01:41,230 --> 00:01:43,370
When was that?

20
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:47,570
Spring, not long after you moved in.

21
00:01:49,220 --> 00:01:51,600
I see.

22
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:54,380
I wish I had known back then.

23
00:01:54,380 --> 00:01:56,420
You think so?

24
00:01:58,670 --> 00:02:01,520
- Have you been to our store before? 
 - What?

25
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:05,000
I used to watch the store for my mom often.

26
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:07,600
   

27
00:02:08,510 --> 00:02:11,780
Have you ever rented a DVD from us?

28
00:02:14,180 --> 00:02:16,360
I don't know why I'm so sleepy.

29
00:02:17,980 --> 00:02:19,550
Are you...

30
00:02:19,550 --> 00:02:21,430
Are you going to sleep?

31
00:02:22,330 --> 00:02:24,790
Yeah, I'm so sleepy.

32
00:02:37,970 --> 00:02:39,930
Go in.

33
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:56,280
 We live our lives missing so many things. 

34
00:02:56,280 --> 00:03:03,100
 Sun Jae used to be someone so far away, like a star in the sky. 

35
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:09,640
 At the end of my teens, full of memories I wish I didn't remember, 

36
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:14,750
 Sun Jae was always there within my arm's reach. 

37
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:21,740
 Breathing the same air, looking at the same sky, every day. 

38
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:24,560
 Walking the same streets. 

39
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,790
 He knew my name. 

40
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:29,730
 Hey! Im Sol! 

41
00:03:29,730 --> 00:03:32,490
 He saved me. 

42
00:03:32,490 --> 00:03:34,940
 I didn't know that back then. 

43
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:42,830
 How many moments of connection have I missed in my life? 

44
00:03:42,830 --> 00:03:46,840
 I realized it only after facing my past again. 

45
00:03:48,310 --> 00:03:50,950
 Why are you crying? 

46
00:03:50,950 --> 00:03:55,470
 Maybe those moments that I shouldn't have missed 

47
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:58,360
 were shining somewhere, 

48
00:03:58,360 --> 00:04:02,890
 sending me signals all this time. 

49
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:06,010
 So that I won't miss those signals, 

50
00:04:06,010 --> 00:04:08,870
 that may be why I'm here. 

51
00:04:08,870 --> 00:04:13,560
 Could it be why you and I met again? 

52
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,090
   

53
00:04:19,090 --> 00:04:22,130
 Sun Jae! Ryu Sun Jae! 

54
00:04:24,540 --> 00:04:26,860
 Sun Jae! 

55
00:04:28,340 --> 00:04:30,650
Sun Jae!

56
00:04:35,030 --> 00:04:37,010
Oh, Sun Jae!

57
00:04:37,810 --> 00:04:39,330
Sun Jae! Come outside for a second.

58
00:04:39,330 --> 00:04:41,670
What is it now?

59
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:51,300
Sun Jae, look at the sky! There's a rainbow.

60
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:52,500
Isn't it pretty?

61
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,770
If I hadn't woken you up, you would have missed it!

62
00:04:54,770 --> 00:04:57,050
Make a wish. Quick!

63
00:04:57,050 --> 00:04:59,440
What is she seeing?

64
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:05,090
What? Can't you see it?

65
00:05:05,090 --> 00:05:06,700
No.

66
00:05:08,910 --> 00:05:10,740
One second.

67
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:16,600
Sun Jae!

68
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:35,430
♫  I can hear it anywhere, I can feel it  ♫

69
00:05:35,430 --> 00:05:38,560
How is it? Can you see it now?

70
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:40,230
Yeah.

71
00:05:40,230 --> 00:05:44,050
♫  Countless nights and darkness are alright with you here  ♫

72
00:05:44,050 --> 00:05:48,400
♫  Even when it's exhausting  ♫

73
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:52,850
♫  I know I can reach you  ♫

74
00:05:52,850 --> 00:06:01,300
♫  You became my miracle  ♫

75
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:05,610
♫  Tell me, I love you  ♫

76
00:06:05,610 --> 00:06:10,010
♫  I'll always be by your side  ♫

77
00:06:10,010 --> 00:06:15,550
♫  All my time, all my days with you  ♫

78
00:06:15,550 --> 00:06:20,690
♫  Just you and I, you and I  ♫

79
00:06:20,690 --> 00:06:24,260
♫  You and I, just you and I  ♫

80
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:27,890
Oh, my! What? What is this cold water?

81
00:06:27,890 --> 00:06:29,470
You brat!

82
00:06:29,470 --> 00:06:33,760
You're too old to be playing with water! This is very cold! Hey!

83
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:36,010
Wait right there!

84
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:41,970
Hey! What are you doing?

85
00:06:41,970 --> 00:06:44,430
- Mom! Mom! 
 - What are you doing with this!

86
00:06:44,430 --> 00:06:46,300
Mom, I'll turn it off. I'll turn it off!

87
00:06:46,300 --> 00:06:48,660
Mom, calm down. Seriously, calm down.

88
00:06:48,660 --> 00:06:50,540
Mom, hold on! Hold on!

89
00:06:50,540 --> 00:06:53,310
You are way too old to be playing with water!

90
00:06:53,310 --> 00:06:56,160
Mom, listen to me.

91
00:06:58,770 --> 00:07:00,700
 I'm begging you, please! 

92
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:03,240
 I'm sorry! I'm sorry! 

93
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:06,260
 - Please! 
 - Stop right there! 

94
00:07:16,140 --> 00:07:18,130
Sun Jae!

95
00:07:19,510 --> 00:07:21,090
Here.

96
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:25,270
What is it? What are you giving me this morning?

97
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:32,670
It flew off of your rooftop.

98
00:07:32,670 --> 00:07:35,950
T-This isn't mine. It's my grandma's!

99
00:07:35,950 --> 00:07:38,140
My grandma likes pink.

100
00:07:38,140 --> 00:07:41,720
What? I didn't ask.

101
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:45,820
Crap!

102
00:07:45,820 --> 00:07:47,960
I was going to ask you to walk to school together.

103
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:50,680
I have something I want to do with you.

104
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,530
What is it?

105
00:07:52,530 --> 00:07:54,640
You'll see.

106
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:00,330
Thank you, Sun Jae.

107
00:08:00,330 --> 00:08:01,550
For what?

108
00:08:01,550 --> 00:08:03,300
For saving my life.

109
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:05,670
And I'm sorry.

110
00:08:05,670 --> 00:08:09,050
I should have thanked you before.

111
00:08:09,050 --> 00:08:10,450
I'm late.

112
00:08:10,450 --> 00:08:12,490
You told me yesterday.

113
00:08:12,490 --> 00:08:15,520
Yesterday is yesterday.

114
00:08:17,900 --> 00:08:19,510
So, you're not avoiding me anymore.

115
00:08:19,510 --> 00:08:21,310
I thought you didn't make friends with girls.

116
00:08:21,310 --> 00:08:23,120
Who said I'd be your friend?

117
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:27,630
 So, all those "Just friends" rumors were all real romances. 

118
00:08:27,630 --> 00:08:30,980
 You dated a lot of people, huh? 

119
00:08:30,980 --> 00:08:33,520
Fine, then you can be my lifesaver.

120
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:35,730
I'll be the magpie that returns the good deed.

121
00:08:35,730 --> 00:08:38,640
I thought it was a swallow.

122
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:40,560
Was it?

123
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:49,200
♫  If you never talk, I'll never leave you  ♫

124
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:54,920
That was dangerous.

125
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:59,430
Then... should I be a swallow?

126
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:06,230
You brought a whole gourd.

127
00:09:06,230 --> 00:09:07,420
It's a time capsule.

128
00:09:07,420 --> 00:09:10,400
I put a present for you inside.

129
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:14,600
In folktales, precious gems come out of gourds.

130
00:09:15,460 --> 00:09:16,710
I thought it was a present.

131
00:09:16,710 --> 00:09:19,490
Can't you just give it to me? Why work so hard to bury it in the ground? Is it kimchi?

132
00:09:19,490 --> 00:09:22,860
It's not a kimchi jar. It's a time capsule.

133
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:25,110
Come on, help me dig.

134
00:09:27,510 --> 00:09:29,320
What's in it, then?

135
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:32,300
Is it really a precious gem?

136
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:36,850
Something even more rare and special than that.

137
00:09:36,850 --> 00:09:39,140
You'll be so surprised when you open it later.

138
00:09:39,140 --> 00:09:41,550
When is later?

139
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:43,480
Maybe around 2023?

140
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:45,530
What kind of present sits there for that long?

141
00:09:45,530 --> 00:09:47,290
It's like stock shares.

142
00:09:47,290 --> 00:09:51,190
Like a blue chip! You want to sit on it for a long time.

143
00:09:51,190 --> 00:09:52,700
Really?

144
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:54,550
No, it's fake.

145
00:09:58,410 --> 00:10:04,450
At midnight on January 1st, 2023, let's meet on the Han River bridge.

146
00:10:04,450 --> 00:10:06,220
Let's take it out together that day.

147
00:10:06,220 --> 00:10:08,550
Why does it have to be that day?

148
00:10:10,820 --> 00:10:13,930
   

149
00:10:16,780 --> 00:10:19,410
 So that I can change your fate. 

150
00:10:19,410 --> 00:10:23,640
 So please... stay alive just one more day. 

151
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:27,990
It's a gift that will only be meaningful on that day.

152
00:10:27,990 --> 00:10:32,330
It's a very, very big gift, so look forward to it.

153
00:10:32,330 --> 00:10:34,080
Don't take it out before that. Okay?

154
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:37,350
At midnight on January 1st, 2023. The Han River Bridge.

155
00:10:37,350 --> 00:10:40,540
Remember. Okay?

156
00:10:40,540 --> 00:10:44,350
On January 1st, 2023. The Han River Bridge.

157
00:10:44,350 --> 00:10:47,600
At midnight, the Han River Bridge...

158
00:10:48,390 --> 00:10:51,980
Wait, aren't you going to see me until then?

159
00:10:51,980 --> 00:10:54,280
You never know what will happen.

160
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:57,300
Even if we drift apart from each others' lives,

161
00:10:57,300 --> 00:10:59,570
please come meet me that day.

162
00:10:59,570 --> 00:11:01,910
Like going to a school reunion. Okay?

163
00:11:01,910 --> 00:11:04,860
Like going to see an old friend.

164
00:11:04,860 --> 00:11:07,490
Who said I was your friend?

165
00:11:15,830 --> 00:11:17,100
 Hey, I'm busy. 

166
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:20,210
 If you see Im Sol around the corner, see if she's hurt. 

167
00:11:20,210 --> 00:11:22,390
 Why would I see her? Ask Kim Tae Sung. 

168
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:24,460
 He's not dating Im Sol because he likes her. 

169
00:11:24,460 --> 00:11:26,700
 - He won't check on her. 
 - What? 

170
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:29,450
 There's a girl named Choi Ga Hyun who follows him around. 

171
00:11:29,450 --> 00:11:32,770
 He just wants to date someone to get rid of her. 

172
00:11:32,770 --> 00:11:34,680
Hey, you...

173
00:11:35,710 --> 00:11:38,200
Never mind. Let's go.

174
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:40,710
She can't see through people.

175
00:11:41,350 --> 00:11:45,150
Hey! Where are your eyes?

176
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:46,870
Here?

177
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:50,940
Wait for me!

178
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:56,770
What's with disciplinary lately? Always picking at our uniforms!

179
00:11:56,770 --> 00:11:58,520
I know!

180
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:01,950
I forgot my tie!

181
00:12:01,950 --> 00:12:05,070
I'm going to have to run laps.

182
00:12:05,070 --> 00:12:06,850
Hold on.

183
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:26,330
What about you?

184
00:12:26,330 --> 00:12:28,640
I was an athlete, you know.

185
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:31,190
I never wore my uniform anyway.

186
00:12:31,190 --> 00:12:32,960
They won't pick on me.

187
00:12:37,140 --> 00:12:38,600
Look at your tie.

188
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:40,230
Don't you wash your clothes?

189
00:12:40,230 --> 00:12:42,830
You little bastards.

190
00:12:42,830 --> 00:12:44,900
You.

191
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:47,920
Hey, Ryu Sun Jae. You're not an athlete anymore.

192
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:50,060
Wear your uniform properly, got it?

193
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:51,810
- Yes. 
 - Hello, Teacher.

194
00:12:51,810 --> 00:12:54,060
What's up with you?

195
00:12:54,060 --> 00:12:55,730
To what do I owe the pleasure?

196
00:12:55,730 --> 00:12:58,980
You rats used to climb over the wall to get away.

197
00:12:58,980 --> 00:13:02,910
We... are turning ourselves in.

198
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:04,500
You'll take that into consideration. Right?

199
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:06,560
Of course!

200
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:08,380
Come over here.

201
00:13:10,510 --> 00:13:11,780
I thought I'd seen it all.

202
00:13:11,780 --> 00:13:14,330
The last place does seven more laps.

203
00:13:14,330 --> 00:13:16,590
Why did you drag me into this, dude?

204
00:13:16,590 --> 00:13:18,940
You need to get some exercise.

205
00:13:23,670 --> 00:13:25,220
Hey.

206
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:28,300
You won't even say hi?

207
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:30,800
Are we even close enough to do that?

208
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:33,720
Then, how do you know my girlfriend?

209
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:36,170
Why are you getting punished instead of her?

210
00:13:39,090 --> 00:13:42,400
Right, aren't you neighbors with Sol?

211
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:44,080
What do you want to know?

212
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:46,090
What do I want to know?

213
00:13:46,090 --> 00:13:50,370
Are swimmers better at swimming or running?

214
00:13:51,170 --> 00:13:55,080
Turtles are fast in the ocean but mega slow on land.

215
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:56,990
Are you like that, too?

216
00:14:17,770 --> 00:14:20,040
Quit smoking!

217
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:15,500
What the heck?

218
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:18,220
Why are you staring at me like that? Gross.

219
00:15:22,210 --> 00:15:24,810
- Just confirming. 
 - You're crazy!

220
00:15:24,810 --> 00:15:26,380
What do you mean, confirming?

221
00:15:26,380 --> 00:15:30,040
I'm so right. You really like Im Sol, huh?

222
00:15:30,040 --> 00:15:32,650
- What? 
 - Look at how you've been lately.

223
00:15:32,650 --> 00:15:35,780
You never skip school. You don't smoke.

224
00:15:35,780 --> 00:15:38,250
When girls want to see you, you run off by yourself.

225
00:15:38,250 --> 00:15:39,400
You're acting weird.

226
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:41,920
Hey! Hey! Put your clothes on!

227
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:43,960
This is visual terrorism.

228
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:45,910
My eyes are bleeding.

229
00:15:45,910 --> 00:15:49,280
- You don't like it? 
 - Get dressed!

230
00:15:50,490 --> 00:15:52,420
 - Didn't he lose to him last time?  
  - Correct. 

231
00:15:52,420 --> 00:15:54,390
 He must be looking for an opportunity for payback. 

232
00:15:54,390 --> 00:15:58,090
 To the left, South Korea's Park Tae Hwan. To the right, the red cap... 

233
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:02,560
 Freestyle! 

234
00:16:02,560 --> 00:16:04,290
 Ready... 

235
00:16:06,490 --> 00:16:08,350
What?

236
00:16:08,350 --> 00:16:09,980
Why isn't it turning off?

237
00:16:09,980 --> 00:16:11,980
 Park Tae Hwan... 

238
00:16:11,980 --> 00:16:15,430
 Zhang Lin's head emerges first... 

239
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:19,770
 We predict that much for the 200m. 

240
00:16:21,630 --> 00:16:23,550
I'm home.

241
00:16:23,550 --> 00:16:26,050
Hey. You're home.

242
00:16:26,050 --> 00:16:28,440
What are you doing?

243
00:16:30,380 --> 00:16:33,550
The TV is broken.

244
00:16:35,970 --> 00:16:38,260
What's going on with the floor?

245
00:16:38,260 --> 00:16:40,520
There was a rat.

246
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:42,510
 He's leading, leading, leading! 

247
00:16:42,510 --> 00:16:44,390
Goodness, he is so good-looking.

248
00:16:44,390 --> 00:16:49,260
His mother is so fortunate to have such a great son.

249
00:16:49,260 --> 00:16:50,580
Oh, my, Park Tae Hwan!

250
00:16:50,580 --> 00:16:52,370
Is he going to win the gold tomorrow?

251
00:16:52,370 --> 00:16:53,880
Looks like it.

252
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:55,870
A gold medal for swimming for South Korea?

253
00:16:55,870 --> 00:16:59,910
We were lucky to get through the first round.

254
00:16:59,910 --> 00:17:00,910
It's possible!

255
00:17:00,910 --> 00:17:05,310
 Gold medal? He even won the silver to win two. 

256
00:17:05,310 --> 00:17:06,920
 That dumbass. 

257
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:10,180
 That's why you lost everything in the stock market. 

258
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:12,590
 Huh? Hold on. 

259
00:17:17,490 --> 00:17:19,960
   

260
00:17:38,430 --> 00:17:41,150
   

261
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:49,360
 Sun Jae, do you have time tomorrow? 

262
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:54,750
♫  I feel this strange feeling  ♫

263
00:17:54,750 --> 00:18:00,270
♫  My heart is beating, I'm dizzy  ♫

264
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:02,680
♫  Will it be embarrassing to say, "I miss you?"  ♫

265
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:04,390
What's up?

266
00:18:04,390 --> 00:18:06,210
Want to see a movie with me?

267
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:07,840
What? A movie?

268
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:10,610
